**Overall Meaning:**

"I am eternal, faultless, inactive, pure, spotless, without duality, without a name, and steady."

This verse emphasizes the perfect and unchanging nature of Brahman. It states that Brahman is eternal, free from all imperfections, beyond all activity, pure, without any qualities or duality, nameless, and unshakeable. It is the ultimate reality, the source of all existence, and the ultimate peace. 
